	9.






	INCOME
	TAXES






	  


	During the three months
	ended March 31, 2017 and 2016, the Company incurred tax expense of approximately $95,000 and $36,000, respectively, on
	foreign income generated by the Company’s CTSAS subsidiary. The
	remaining income tax expense reflected for the three months ended March 31, 2017 and 2016, respectively, reflects tax expense
	on U.S. income generated. Due to management’s assessment that it is more likely than not that a portion of certain
	deferred tax assets may not be realized, the Company has a valuation allowance of approximately $11.8 million as of March 31,
	2017 against its U.S. deferred tax asset, which was generated primarily as a result of foreign tax credits and net operating
	losses.


	 








	 



